Sean was there for his
youthful good looks.

16:19.814 --> 16:22.948
I was there for my tenor voice.

16:22.950 --> 16:26.652
And you know what they said?
The cognoscenti?

16:26.654 --> 16:29.288
Pinky Steuben is going
to be a star, they said.

16:29.290 --> 16:31.090
Not Sean Connery.

16:31.092 --> 16:33.158
Pinky fucking Steuben.

16:33.160 --> 16:37.930
But, as we both know,
that was not meant to be.

16:37.932 --> 16:40.466
I mean, these days Sean Connery
could run me down...

16:40.468 --> 16:42.601
In his rolls Royce and he
wouldn't know who I was.

16:42.603 --> 16:44.470
Unless I told him or sang
for him.

16:44.472 --> 16:46.672
Which would be highly unlikely
if I was lying dead...

16:46.674 --> 16:49.308
Under the wheels of his car.

16:49.310 --> 16:50.943
Ray!

16:50.945 --> 16:54.046
Top of the morning to ya,
me old cocker...

16:54.048 --> 16:58.183
On this blessed
Christmas Eve day?

16:59.953 --> 17:03.789
Oh, B's back from Florida.

17:03.791 --> 17:06.892
Before Christmas?
Mm.

17:06.894 --> 17:09.461
Well, that don't compute.
Hm.

17:09.463 --> 17:12.464
Are the checks in yet?
No.

17:12.465 --> 17:14.032
Oh, well, it's a bit early,
isn't it?

17:14.035 --> 17:15.701
Who the fuck am I talking to?

17:15.703 --> 17:18.203
Rump man... Pete.

17:18.204 --> 17:19.972
Pete.

17:19.973 --> 17:22.141
Well, I'm certainly glad
it's not Helen.

17:22.143 --> 17:25.077
'Cause she looks really awful.
Ha, ha, ha.

17:25.079 --> 17:28.146
Pete, me old cocker.
How the heck are you?

17:28.148 --> 17:31.250
I like that name. You know what?

17:31.252 --> 17:34.053
Sounds like an astronaut.

17:34.055 --> 17:38.023
Now, Pete... look, I hope you
don't mind me saying this, Pete.

17:38.025 --> 17:39.725
But I have this thing.

17:39.727 --> 17:43.529
It... it's a salesman's gift.
I know people.

17:43.531 --> 17:46.532
You understand what I mean?
I know people.

17:46.534 --> 17:49.234
And I can tell just looking
at you now...

17:49.236 --> 17:52.738
That you are going to be
a giant in this business.

17:52.740 --> 17:56.241
Pete, you are going to
be a captain of industry.

17:56.243 --> 18:01.046
In fact, you actually
remind me of old bibby himself.

18:01.048 --> 18:02.448
Bibby?

18:02.450 --> 18:05.684
Ah, our nickname for our
beloved employer, Mr. Bibideaux.

18:05.686 --> 18:07.453
There is something
in the eyes, you see.

18:07.455 --> 18:10.422
There is something in the eyes.
They are sharp.

18:10.424 --> 18:13.525
They are very, very sharp.

18:13.527 --> 18:15.260
Ray.
Pinky.

18:15.262 --> 18:18.897
Um, I need a break, but...

18:18.899 --> 18:21.133
you're shy of funds.

18:23.536 --> 18:27.806
A mind reader... a regular
Edgar Cayce, this man.

18:27.808 --> 18:32.244
Hey, Ray, you don't think
that young Pete...

18:32.246 --> 18:35.781
do you think that Pete
is feeling Christian?

18:35.783 --> 18:36.482
I couldn't speak for him.

18:36.484 --> 18:38.283
Well, of course you
couldn't speak for him, Ray.

18:38.285 --> 18:40.083
Of course, you
couldn't speak for him.

18:40.085 --> 18:42.888
Only Pete can speak for Pete.

18:42.890 --> 18:45.891
So what say you, Pete,
old chap, hm?

18:45.893 --> 18:47.593
Help out a friend?

18:50.063 --> 18:54.066
I think I've got...
I've got five dollars.

18:54.068 --> 18:55.734
But that's for lunch.

18:55.736 --> 18:57.669
Maybe Ray could break it.

18:57.671 --> 19:00.339
Oh, Ray won't let you
anywhere near his register.

19:00.341 --> 19:02.608
Guards it like fort Knox.

19:02.610 --> 19:05.577
I, however, may be
able to help you out.

19:05.579 --> 19:06.845
But...

19:06.847 --> 19:08.514
he won't let me near it, either.

19:12.118 --> 19:14.820
Oh, he himself has said it...

19:14.822 --> 19:19.625
And it's frightening,
to his credit.

19:19.627 --> 19:23.028
Oh, you gorgeous, buxom thing,
you.

19:23.030 --> 19:25.264
<i>Woman
welcome, valley shoppers...</i>

19:25.266 --> 19:26.999
<i>To the green
at green meadows mall.</i>

19:27.001 --> 19:30.669
<i>It's now 10:00 A.M.
enjoy your shopping day.</i>

19:39.445 --> 19:44.850
Dave? Ha-hey!
You're never gonna get it.

19:44.852 --> 19:49.221
Oh, well, guess. Why can't you
guess? It's just a...

19:49.223 --> 19:53.692
penny... Wednesday.

19:53.694 --> 19:57.062
Penny Wednesday...
From Grossinger's?

19:58.565 --> 20:04.169
The phone book... yeah,
you're right here on page 113.

20:05.939 --> 20:10.042
Hold on a sec.
You off your meds?

20:11.444 --> 20:14.580
It's nothing, Dave, just some
creep smitten with my beauty.

20:14.582 --> 20:16.181
<i>Receptionist
Mr. Nakimura's office.</i>

20:16.183 --> 20:18.650
Ah, yes, hi, good morning.
Mr. Nakimura, please?

20:18.652 --> 20:21.486
You said call if I ever
made it down.

20:21.488 --> 20:22.754
Well, I'm down.

20:22.756 --> 20:24.256
<i>Receptionist
may I ask who's calling?</i>

20:24.258 --> 20:26.258
Yes, this is Ray Lapine.

20:26.260 --> 20:28.060
Just for the day.

20:28.062 --> 20:30.495
Unless I can find
some place to stay.

20:30.497 --> 20:33.565
<i>Receptionist
we have your information.</i>

20:33.567 --> 20:35.334
Oh, you have it. Excellent.

20:35.336 --> 20:37.369
I didn't call for money.

20:37.371 --> 20:41.106
I just... thought we had a love
connection, that's all.

20:41.108 --> 20:43.842
Is there another time
today that I could call back?

20:43.844 --> 20:46.078
<i>Receptionist maybe
try him in an hour and a half.</i>

20:46.080 --> 20:49.748
Okay, that's fine. 90 minutes.
Can we commit to that?

20:49.750 --> 20:50.949
<i>Receptionist
you'll just have to try him.</i>

20:50.951 --> 20:53.185
<i>Merry Christmas.</i>
Yes, Merry Chr...

20:53.187 --> 20:57.522
tonight? You got a wife,
don't you, Dave?

20:57.524 --> 20:59.558
You swore up and down you
didn't...

20:59.560 --> 21:02.127
And I am just stupid enough.

21:02.129 --> 21:04.763
I'm not so stupid,
I don't know I'm dumb, okay?

21:08.401 --> 21:12.804
Hey. Employment booth.
Second level.

21:12.806 --> 21:16.074
Tell Lorraine that
Ray Lapine sent you.

21:16.076 --> 21:20.312
Yeah... and why would
Ray Lapine do that?

21:25.218 --> 21:30.255
Whatever it is, he's not
gonna let it go.

21:30.257 --> 21:33.225
That's Ray, you see,
he's like the Irish.

21:33.227 --> 21:35.560
He loves his misery.

21:35.562 --> 21:39.064
Talking of misery,
are you married?

21:39.066 --> 21:42.467
No, of course you're not,
of course, you're not.

21:42.469 --> 21:46.838
You're a living example of that
proposition which states...

21:46.840 --> 21:51.009
Not all men are fools,
some are bachelors.

21:51.011 --> 21:52.778
Ba-boom.

22:06.893 --> 22:09.094
So, you're married?

22:09.096 --> 22:10.996
Oh, five times.

22:13.700 --> 22:19.938
Yep. Five times married and
five beautiful wives.

22:19.940 --> 22:23.342
Now once, on my honeymoon
with Lorna.

22:23.344 --> 22:28.213
Lorna, French Canadian,
god, was she hot.

22:28.215 --> 22:33.719
We were a couple.
I mounted her like a stallion.

22:33.721 --> 22:37.823
This was not lovemaking in a
convention sense, Pete.

22:37.825 --> 22:42.127
This was more like some
sort of nature film.

22:51.304 --> 22:53.505
Hey. What's going on
down there?

22:55.241 --> 22:58.477
Something new... there's always
something new.

22:58.479 --> 23:01.246
Yeah.

23:03.349 --> 23:06.818
You want to get laid and I know
you do... where do you go, eh?

23:06.820 --> 23:09.888
Bars? Parties? Night clubs?

23:09.890 --> 23:11.323
Wrong!

23:11.325 --> 23:12.991
Wrong.

23:12.993 --> 23:16.027
Launderettes.

23:16.029 --> 23:18.096
There are women there, Pete.

23:18.098 --> 23:20.165
I Grant you, most of them
are married...

23:20.167 --> 23:24.202
But there are bona fide women
there nonetheless.

23:24.204 --> 23:31.009
And did you know the incidents
of venereal disease...

23:31.011 --> 23:36.281
Transmission in launderettes
is low.

23:36.283 --> 23:37.616
Really?

23:37.618 --> 23:40.185
Extremely low.

23:40.187 --> 23:42.354
And I am speaking
from experience here.

23:42.356 --> 23:43.555
Yeah.

23:43.557 --> 23:44.689
And you know the best thing?

23:44.691 --> 23:46.858
No pretension... no hard to get.

23:46.860 --> 23:49.795
It's just eye contact besides
the industrial dryers...

23:49.797 --> 23:52.564
And two minutes later, you're
doing it on top of the Maytag.

23:52.566 --> 23:55.400
And do you know how
they look afterwards?

23:55.402 --> 23:58.270
How?
Grateful. And why?

23:58.272 --> 24:01.440
And this is the best part...
no pretension.

24:04.343 --> 24:06.445
I thought that was
the best part.

24:06.447 --> 24:07.813
Nah.

24:07.815 --> 24:10.449
You're a very literal soul,
aren't you.

24:11.551 --> 24:17.656
Oh! As I live and breathe,
here is the man.

24:17.658 --> 24:20.792
How are you, Tony?
How are things?

24:20.794 --> 24:24.763
52 bucks, pinky. And I want it
by Monday, no more bullshit.

24:24.765 --> 24:27.432
And you shall have it.

24:27.434 --> 24:29.801
Any news about the checks?

24:29.803 --> 24:30.969
They're not here yet.

24:30.971 --> 24:33.905
B-but... why not?

24:33.907 --> 24:36.575
Paramus, Pearl river,
white plains.

24:36.577 --> 24:39.911
Ah, but not in Nanuet.

24:39.913 --> 24:42.681
They weren't ready yet.
No.

24:42.683 --> 24:45.951
I expect they will be
by tonight, yeah?

24:45.953 --> 24:51.823
Well, happy Christmas to you
and yours.

24:51.825 --> 24:53.325
Monday.

24:54.627 --> 24:56.761
Drunk ass motherfucker.

25:13.479 --> 25:15.480
Who are you, Wayne Newton?

25:16.415 --> 25:19.885
Felix Potemkin, mall manager.

25:23.289 --> 25:24.556
Yeah.

25:27.393 --> 25:28.894
I have a friend.

25:28.896 --> 25:31.463
No names, at the moment,
because we're just supposing...

25:31.465 --> 25:34.966
Two perfect strangers talking
for an instant in eternity...

25:34.968 --> 25:36.635
Neither wanting
anything from the other.

25:36.637 --> 25:38.236
Is this a long story?

25:39.505 --> 25:42.474
Perhaps I can be helpful
with your employment situation.

25:42.476 --> 25:44.743
Following which you
might join me for lunch...

25:44.745 --> 25:47.345
At my private table
in the Macy's tea room?

25:49.181 --> 25:51.082
Are you a spaz or what?

25:51.084 --> 25:55.587
Maybe I'm that candy-colored
clown, maybe not.

25:59.792 --> 26:02.394
I'll think about it.
Okay.

26:11.338 --> 26:13.371
Come in. May I help you?

27:00.486 --> 27:03.088
Mr. Lapine...

27:03.090 --> 27:04.789
What are you doing?

27:07.893 --> 27:11.596
Quality control...
Checking the exposure.

27:11.598 --> 27:14.799
Grain... paper quality.

27:17.737 --> 27:19.671
Well, aren't those private?

27:19.673 --> 27:22.941
Let me ask you a question.
What do you think?

27:22.943 --> 27:24.476
Oh, god.

27:24.478 --> 27:27.846
Yeah, do you think
she's having fun?

27:27.848 --> 27:30.849
I don't think she's
a Wharton girl.

27:30.851 --> 27:36.488
Maybe Julliard. Oh yeah...
Flautist.

27:36.490 --> 27:39.257
You recognize the guy
in that thing?

27:39.259 --> 27:40.992
Maybe from the club?

27:44.764 --> 27:48.767
That's Dr. Lobell.
He's a gynecologist.

27:50.536 --> 27:52.103
Appears he is.

27:55.708 --> 27:58.643
I don't think that's his wife.

27:58.645 --> 28:01.846
Uh, no, I don't think so.
Oh-o.

28:01.848 --> 28:04.049
But that is.

28:06.752 --> 28:08.687
Mrs. lobell...

28:13.559 --> 28:17.228
Well, hi there, Pete.
What are you doing here?

28:17.230 --> 28:20.131
I'm just working for a paycheck.

28:20.133 --> 28:21.900
Young Peter and I were
just discussing you.

28:21.902 --> 28:23.368
Oh?

28:23.370 --> 28:25.570
Actually I was defending you
and the doctor.

28:25.572 --> 28:27.572
I was defending your choice...

28:27.574 --> 28:29.641
Of taking your business
to Yorktown camera.

28:29.643 --> 28:30.575
I mean, here at bibideaux...

28:30.577 --> 28:33.344
All we can do is offer
25 years of unflagging service.

28:33.346 --> 28:36.648
Yorktown is cheaper.

28:36.650 --> 28:37.315
And certainly I don't mean
that in a tawdry way.

28:37.317 --> 28:38.483
I really have to run.

28:38.485 --> 28:39.584
But let me just finish...

28:39.586 --> 28:44.022
Because I was very surprised by
some of the photos...

28:44.024 --> 28:46.091
That Peter here has
just come across.

28:46.093 --> 28:49.861
Interesting tidbit
about our young Peter.

28:49.863 --> 28:52.097
He likes going through
the photographs.

28:52.099 --> 28:55.166
Quality control, he calls it.

28:55.168 --> 28:56.568
I can't quite explain how
it happened...

28:56.570 --> 28:58.703
But it seems as though we've
come across some photographs...

28:58.705 --> 29:00.171
Of your husband's.

29:00.173 --> 29:04.442
Oh, I... I doubt they're
my husband's.

29:04.444 --> 29:08.279
Ah, how is the good doctor,
by the way?

29:08.281 --> 29:10.782
I thought you knew.

29:10.784 --> 29:12.250
What's that?

29:13.352 --> 29:16.955
They have... they found
a brain tumor.

29:21.694 --> 29:24.963
Um, how long ago?

29:24.965 --> 29:27.766
About a month.

29:27.768 --> 29:30.735
They've done everything
that they can, so...

29:30.870 --> 29:33.438
Mr. Lapine...
I'm so sorry.

29:33.440 --> 29:35.106
These are not your husband's
photos...

29:35.108 --> 29:37.075
At all, Mrs. lobell.

29:37.077 --> 29:39.544
See, Peter, no,
the last name is Lapell.

29:39.546 --> 29:43.648
I'm... I am terribly sorry.
Big mistake.

29:43.650 --> 29:47.085
Please do tell your husband
for me and from everyone here...

29:47.087 --> 29:48.553
I will.

29:51.524 --> 29:53.625
She didn't let me
finish my sentence.

30:16.015 --> 30:17.248
Hey!

30:21.554 --> 30:23.188
I'm sorry.

30:26.458 --> 30:30.495
I'm okay, just gonna stink
for a while.

30:40.239 --> 30:41.873
How... how did you fall in?

30:41.875 --> 30:45.176
Fall? I climbed in,
looking for breakfast.

30:46.212 --> 30:48.146
Not for me, Dorko.

30:56.889 --> 30:59.624
Wow... look at him go.

30:59.626 --> 31:01.125
Her.

31:01.127 --> 31:03.494
And she's hungry.

31:03.496 --> 31:05.897
Vegetarian... just like
her mama.

31:05.899 --> 31:08.867
Poor thing, ain't had
a bite since Kingston.

31:11.103 --> 31:13.738
You want to buy her?
She could use a good home.

31:13.740 --> 31:16.641
Me? Bad luck. Everybody around
me always croaks.

31:16.643 --> 31:18.810
Oh.

31:20.412 --> 31:21.846
You could trade me that watch.

31:21.848 --> 31:24.382
That looks like something
captain James T. Kirk...

31:24.384 --> 31:26.417
Of the USS enterprise
would wear.

31:27.987 --> 31:31.489
Who gave it to you?
Your girlfriend?

31:32.625 --> 31:33.591
My mother.

31:37.196 --> 31:39.097
I should get back.
Oh yeah.

31:39.099 --> 31:40.665
For sure, me, too.

31:40.667 --> 31:42.500
It's freezin' out here.

31:42.502 --> 31:46.337
Would you be a gentleman and
walk me the nice way around?

31:49.975 --> 31:53.878
Wait up. Hold my bunny while I
put on my work uniform?

32:00.452 --> 32:02.186
Hi.

32:02.188 --> 32:03.788
Wow.

32:03.790 --> 32:06.925
Um, I think she's okay.

32:06.927 --> 32:10.428
Cool. I don't want to sell
her anyways.

32:10.430 --> 32:13.031
She and me are going to Paris.

32:13.033 --> 32:14.365
She and I.

32:14.367 --> 32:18.102
She and <i> I</i> are going to Paris.

32:18.104 --> 32:19.904
That's what I said.

32:31.016 --> 32:32.250
Really.

32:33.652 --> 32:36.220
They tried to steal
the Oscar Meyer Weinermobile?

32:36.222 --> 32:38.890
See, Jo Jo and my other
brother Tommy, the fuck up?

32:38.892 --> 32:40.658
They stole the Weinermobile
and were trying to get away...

32:40.660 --> 32:41.993
When the cops showed
up and chased them.

32:43.762 --> 32:45.897
It's not as if you can
hope to blend into traffic.

32:45.899 --> 32:47.899
Stupid, huh?

32:47.901 --> 32:49.334
Oh, it was terrible.

32:49.336 --> 32:50.935
My one brother is in prison
for stealing the truck...

32:50.937 --> 32:52.403
And for running my
other brother over.

32:52.405 --> 32:54.439
I'm sorry.

32:55.941 --> 32:58.176
No, I made it up.

32:58.178 --> 33:01.446
Jo Jo got shot knocking
over a pink dot in L.A.

33:01.448 --> 33:03.681
Poor Mook.

33:03.683 --> 33:05.283
Didn't have a pigeon angel.

33:07.252 --> 33:09.187
You ever try and run
a pigeon over?

33:09.189 --> 33:11.856
No, I have not.

33:11.858 --> 33:14.625
Oh, you're a liar, too.

33:14.627 --> 33:17.662
See everybody tries to gun
them winged roaches over...

33:17.664 --> 33:20.465
But few succeed. Why?

33:20.467 --> 33:22.333
You come speeding up on
some unsuspecting pigeon...

33:22.335 --> 33:25.803
Just clucking away there on the
tarmac and naturally you gun it.

33:25.805 --> 33:27.805
It's your instinct to try to
nail that thing...

33:27.807 --> 33:28.840
Because we're carnivores.

33:28.842 --> 33:31.109
We crave advantage over
the weak, it's our way.

33:31.111 --> 33:33.144
But that pigeon...

33:33.146 --> 33:34.946
He's developed his
own set of responses...

33:34.948 --> 33:36.280
And gun it as you may...

33:36.282 --> 33:38.783
That little guy always flies
away at the last second.

33:39.918 --> 33:41.285
My theory?

33:41.287 --> 33:43.354
Every pigeon's got a teeny,
little, invisible angel...

33:43.356 --> 33:45.456
Riding on their wings that taps
'em on the shoulder and says...

33:45.458 --> 33:48.192
"Hey, stupid, look
out for the Buick!"

33:50.662 --> 33:52.864
Well, they do have eyes.

33:52.866 --> 33:56.634
Those two little holes that
are in the back of their heads.

33:59.805 --> 34:01.305
Eyes?

34:03.275 --> 34:06.577
Well, they see the car coming.

34:08.179 --> 34:11.916
And at the last second fly away.

34:11.918 --> 34:14.318
I liked my answer better.

34:16.855 --> 34:19.190
Me, too.

34:24.329 --> 34:26.330
Hey, dog ears.

34:29.168 --> 34:31.034
I got it. I got it.

34:31.036 --> 34:32.837
Buy me lunch later?

34:32.839 --> 34:34.705
I got an hour.

35:06.405 --> 35:10.708
Memories, Pete... that is what
we have in our hands.

35:10.710 --> 35:11.876
Of course, in the old days...

35:11.878 --> 35:14.212
The film used to come in here
like a river.

35:43.075 --> 35:44.642
You okay there, buddy?

35:51.083 --> 35:52.450
I'm okay.

35:52.452 --> 35:53.918
All right, take a minute,
if you need it.

35:53.920 --> 35:55.453
Maybe I ain't got a minute.

35:58.590 --> 36:01.325
Polaroid film for my
granddaughter's camera.

36:01.327 --> 36:02.627
I don't know the model.

36:02.629 --> 36:04.462
Cost a heck of a lot
fifteen years back.

36:04.464 --> 36:06.964
Does it like fold flat-like?

36:06.966 --> 36:10.034
Right.
Yeah, XS 70.

36:11.203 --> 36:15.540
Give me... this much.

36:17.209 --> 36:21.279
But don't charge me tax.
I don't pay tax.

36:24.650 --> 36:26.951
Pete, behind you in the shelf
underneath there...

36:26.953 --> 36:28.986
There's a drawer there.

36:30.322 --> 36:32.290
Pete, never mind.

36:33.625 --> 36:34.959
Get out of my store.

36:34.961 --> 36:36.561
Do you want to learn something,
dog ears?

