01:28:41.451 --> 01:28:43.117
Immaterial?

01:28:44.620 --> 01:28:48.022
It's my life, Ray.

01:28:48.024 --> 01:28:51.659
You know what, my old friend? I
should have fired you years ago.

01:28:51.661 --> 01:28:54.495
I'm sorry that I didn't.

01:28:54.497 --> 01:28:58.933
Well, if that's some sort of
apology, I don't need it, mate.

01:28:58.935 --> 01:29:01.869
I know what I am.

01:29:01.871 --> 01:29:05.340
I am an utter fuck up.

01:29:07.076 --> 01:29:09.677
But why did you surrender?

01:29:13.649 --> 01:29:17.118
You know that every
photograph has two sides, right?

01:29:17.120 --> 01:29:22.623
The positive, and the negative.

01:29:27.763 --> 01:29:29.464
You see that?

01:29:29.466 --> 01:29:31.833
See that guy?

01:29:31.835 --> 01:29:35.903
Remember him, 25 years ago?
Me? Huh?

01:29:35.905 --> 01:29:39.841
I mean, not a bad looking guy.

01:29:39.843 --> 01:29:41.709
Pictures don't lie about
that sort of thing, right?

01:29:41.711 --> 01:29:45.046
This guy, me, he was real.
He was real.

01:29:45.048 --> 01:29:47.315
He was a salesman.
He was a businessman.

01:29:49.151 --> 01:29:50.718
A man.

01:29:56.859 --> 01:29:59.594
And then I lost... him.

01:30:01.096 --> 01:30:04.365
And... her.

01:30:04.367 --> 01:30:09.504
And what is left, but
the fucking negative?

01:30:09.506 --> 01:30:12.340
Pinky, I don't even fucking
know who I am, all right?

01:30:12.342 --> 01:30:16.277
That... I don't know anything.
Any more.

01:30:16.279 --> 01:30:19.113
No, fuck that! You know, I do
know one thing, huh?

01:30:19.115 --> 01:30:21.883
We're fucking closing!

01:31:02.024 --> 01:31:04.892
So you'll be okay?
With your check?

01:31:04.894 --> 01:31:07.595
It could probably finance a couple
of those one-hour processors...

01:31:07.597 --> 01:31:08.996
no check.

01:31:12.267 --> 01:31:13.835
But I saw your envelope.

01:31:13.837 --> 01:31:15.403
Yes, but you didn't see
inside the envelope.

01:31:15.405 --> 01:31:17.772
There was no check.
There was a court order, though.

01:31:17.774 --> 01:31:20.408
It seems like all my
funds have been frozen.

01:31:20.410 --> 01:31:21.909
Well, they can't freeze it,
unless they're pressing...

01:31:21.911 --> 01:31:25.012
Criminal charges, they...
hmm.

01:31:29.051 --> 01:31:31.786
I'm... I'm sure you
can get that cleared.

01:31:31.788 --> 01:31:35.823
But your check... there was no
check in the envelope for you.

01:31:35.825 --> 01:31:39.660
Now usually, Christmas staff
is always paid...

01:31:39.662 --> 01:31:41.496
At the end of the shift.

01:31:41.498 --> 01:31:44.599
Unless, of course,
their work isn't done.

01:31:52.941 --> 01:31:54.876
Ah, he sent you to shop me.

01:31:54.878 --> 01:31:56.777
See if I was stealing
or cooking the books.

01:31:56.779 --> 01:31:59.180
You see anything?
You see me take anything?

01:31:59.182 --> 01:32:03.618
Um, film... a brand new camera.

01:32:03.620 --> 01:32:06.654
You gave me everything.

01:32:06.656 --> 01:32:10.858
Oh, right. Good business
lesson there.

01:32:15.931 --> 01:32:18.666
And what did it cost?
What did he pay you to do this?

01:32:18.668 --> 01:32:20.401
Nothing.

01:32:22.271 --> 01:32:26.707
So why? Why would a person
do that sort of thing?

01:32:28.744 --> 01:32:31.345
The practice.

01:32:33.282 --> 01:32:35.082
Hm.

01:32:39.821 --> 01:32:42.757
You just never know how.

01:33:00.442 --> 01:33:04.245
Hey, junior, can we get
going before I miss Santa?

01:33:04.247 --> 01:33:06.447
Give me a minute.

01:33:21.163 --> 01:33:22.797
What's wrong?

01:33:22.799 --> 01:33:24.932
What was your job in
that store with those men?

01:33:24.934 --> 01:33:27.535
It doesn't matter.

01:33:28.470 --> 01:33:30.104
I got her back.

01:33:37.646 --> 01:33:41.248
Why'd you gotta go do that?
Why?

01:33:43.552 --> 01:33:45.119
I wanted to believe you.

01:33:45.121 --> 01:33:47.755
Penny, forget about
the camera store.

01:33:47.757 --> 01:33:50.625
You said you weren't mean.

01:33:50.627 --> 01:33:52.593
I wanted to listen to
all your little lies...

01:33:52.595 --> 01:33:54.795
And try and understand them.

01:33:54.797 --> 01:33:56.397
I was willing to do all that...

01:33:56.399 --> 01:34:01.402
Because I am tired of being
cold... and I liked you.

01:34:03.071 --> 01:34:05.673
And I thought you liked me.
I do.

01:34:05.675 --> 01:34:07.174
You're a liar.

01:34:07.176 --> 01:34:09.944
I'm a liar?

01:34:09.946 --> 01:34:11.846
You know I saw some
pictures of you today...

01:34:11.848 --> 01:34:14.982
That tell the whole truth
and nothing but the truth.

01:34:14.984 --> 01:34:18.419
Grossinger's.

01:34:18.421 --> 01:34:22.289
The man in them,
Dr. Dave lobell.

01:34:22.291 --> 01:34:24.258
No.

01:34:24.260 --> 01:34:26.794
I know his kids.

01:34:28.130 --> 01:34:29.830
His wife.

01:34:31.633 --> 01:34:33.768
You saw?

01:34:33.770 --> 01:34:35.970
Everything.

01:34:36.872 --> 01:34:40.174
He was sick... dying.

01:34:41.643 --> 01:34:45.046
Okay, okay, let's forget it.

01:34:46.815 --> 01:34:51.052
You want to stay at my
place a couple of nights, okay.

01:34:55.824 --> 01:34:58.459
That's what you think of me?

01:34:59.728 --> 01:35:01.462
It's like a gift two people
give each other...

01:35:01.464 --> 01:35:03.898
Like Christmas presents.

01:35:05.467 --> 01:35:06.867
Okay.

01:35:08.970 --> 01:35:10.638
Let's go.

01:35:11.740 --> 01:35:14.075
It is freezing.

01:35:20.682 --> 01:35:23.851
Eyes in the back of my head.

01:35:26.088 --> 01:35:27.521
What?

01:35:32.094 --> 01:35:34.428
Are you coming with me or not?

01:35:53.849 --> 01:35:56.350
Stay away from me!

01:37:57.272 --> 01:37:58.739
Eh.

01:37:58.741 --> 01:38:01.208
Oh, shit.

01:38:01.210 --> 01:38:04.545
Well, that means you won't be
giving me a lift home then.

01:38:09.517 --> 01:38:11.151
Thought you'd be at the parrot.

01:38:11.153 --> 01:38:16.490
No... populated by lonely,
pathetic, old drunks.

01:38:21.329 --> 01:38:23.764
So this is Christmas.
Uh-huh.

01:38:23.766 --> 01:38:27.067
First Christmas in god knows
how many years...

01:38:27.069 --> 01:38:31.238
I have nothing better
to do than actually enjoy it.

01:38:31.240 --> 01:38:33.107
Christ, it's cold, though,
isn't it?

01:38:33.109 --> 01:38:36.243
But I do love the snow,
you know.

01:38:36.245 --> 01:38:40.547
Makes me think I'm a kid again.
Can do anything at all.

01:38:42.317 --> 01:38:45.052
Do you remember Daphne?

01:38:46.721 --> 01:38:48.122
Wife number four.

01:38:48.124 --> 01:38:52.593
Her daughter, well, my daughter,
actually the only daughter...

01:38:52.595 --> 01:38:55.596
That still speaks to me,
god bless her.

01:38:55.598 --> 01:38:57.932
Anyway, she and that little
prick of a husband of hers...

01:38:57.934 --> 01:39:00.301
Are holding some sort
of a soiree this evening.

01:39:00.303 --> 01:39:01.535
All her kids are going
to be there.

01:39:01.537 --> 01:39:03.270
You should see those kids
when I come.

01:39:03.272 --> 01:39:05.606
I tell you, open the door
and they holler...

01:39:05.608 --> 01:39:08.542
And I'll just give 'em a little,
you know, a little song...

01:39:08.544 --> 01:39:09.944
A little shuffle.

01:39:09.946 --> 01:39:12.446
And they love it.

01:39:12.448 --> 01:39:17.151
Love is too small a word, Ray.
Too small a word.

01:39:19.187 --> 01:39:23.891
So I was thinking I might
just stop by.

01:39:25.927 --> 01:39:27.494
Want to come?

01:39:32.000 --> 01:39:33.667
Why not?

01:39:33.669 --> 01:39:35.235
Good.

01:39:35.704 --> 01:39:36.837
You know the last bus left...

01:39:36.839 --> 01:39:39.640
So wherever we go,
we're hoofing it.

01:39:39.642 --> 01:39:42.977
I've got this feeling.
It's a salesman's gift.

01:39:42.979 --> 01:39:46.080
I've got this feeling that
something marvelous...

01:39:46.082 --> 01:39:48.082
Is gonna happen around
that corner.

01:39:50.018 --> 01:39:54.822
You know what, Ray, been so long
since I've walked anywhere...

01:39:54.824 --> 01:39:57.658
I'm not sure I know the way.

01:39:57.660 --> 01:40:00.327
Don't worry, pinky? I do.

